==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heeler
<hw>Heel"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A cock
that strikes well with his heels or spurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A dependent and subservient hanger-on of a political
patron.</def> <mark>[Political Cant, U. S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The army of hungry <qex>heelers</qex> who do their bidding.</q>
<rj><qau>The Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heelless</ent>⟦br⟧
